OL,3,CLondon councils 'biggest losers' under
OL,4,Cgovernment plans to change funding
OL,6,FThe changes, which will come into
OL,7,Feffect from next year, are being
OL,8,Fconsulted on by ministers.
OL,10,FThe Government plans to create a new
OL,11,Fmethodology to assess local authority
OL,12,Fneeds relatively and factor in
OL,13,Fpopulation and deprivation. It will
OL,14,Falso assess need for adult and
OL,15,Fchildren's services.
OL,17,FOverall spending will fall for 186
OL,18,Fcouncils and rise by the same total
OL,19,Fsum for 161. One in 10 will see a fall
OL,20,Fin overall funding, while one in 10
OL,21,Fwill see an increase of 10% or more.
