OL,3,CLondon councils 'biggest losers' under
OL,4,Cgovernment plans to change funding
OL,6,F"But the changes will sting for those
OL,7,Fcouncils that are assessed to
OL,8,Fcurrently receive too high a share of
OL,9,Fthe overall funding pot, and so which
OL,10,Flose out from moves to align funding
OL,11,Fwith assessed spending needs."
OL,13,FThe proposals are criticised in the
OL,14,Freport as "not particularly
OL,15,Fredistributive to poor, urban areas of
OL,16,FEngland". It cites South Tyneside and
OL,17,FSunderland councils being among those
OL,18,Fto lose out from the reforms as slow
OL,19,Fpopulation growth is accounted for.
