OL,3,CLondon councils 'biggest losers' under
OL,4,Cgovernment plans to change funding
OL,6,FLondon will gain the least, with a
OL,7,Fcash-terms increase in funding of 8%
OL,8,Fin the next three years. Analysis by
OL,9,Fthe London Councils collective has
OL,10,Fhighlighted the risk of the funding
OL,11,F"dramatically underestimating" needs
OL,12,Ffor local services in parts of the
OL,13,Fcapital.
OL,15,FIt noted the city has the highest rate
OL,16,Fof poverty in the country when housing
OL,17,Fcosts are factored in.
